
Q: Can I use linux git clone github repository, make branches, commits then push it back? 
A:  Yes you can use it just like normal git.  The only difference is your remote repository is github now.

Q: How can I control the push access?
A: You don't need password to pull. However you need github username and password to push. 

Q: How could I utilize the github pull request function through linux git?
A: After you push local branches to github, you can initiate the pull requests from github.com 
